There is a trend of young women opting for a shotgun wedding then quickly following through with a divorce.

This is not new as studies have shown this trend in other third-world countries, however it continues to have negative consequences for children.

In an interview with Emma Sinandile, a relationship expert, said children are severely affected by seeing their parents divorce for mere social status.

“Some parents tend to do this for social status, so they don’t look bad in their friend’s eyes or for ‘respect’ among community villagers or relatives when the groom’s family is about to visit. Unfortunately the children are at the bottom of the rungs, they are first to suffer,” says Sinandile.

The harsh reality of the matter plagues these newly divorced families even more as both parents relay their post realism to their children.
